{"id":1910,"date":"2012-01-30T20:21:32","date_gmt":"2012-01-31T01:21:32","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.dailyhadithonline.com\/?p=1910"},"modified":"2021-02-18T08:53:35","modified_gmt":"2021-02-18T04:53:35","slug":"hudud-punishments-due-process","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/01\/30\/hudud-punishments-due-process\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Justice: Applying legal punishments with due process"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Abu Huraira reported: Sa\u2019d ibn &#8216;Ubadah said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, if I find another man with my wife, should I leave him alone until I bring four witnesses?\u201d The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201c<strong>Yes<\/strong>.\u201d Sa\u2019d said, \u201cNever! By the One who sent you with the truth, if that happened to me I would quickly grab the sword!\u201d The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>Listen to what your leader is saying<\/strong>. <strong>Verily, he has a sense of honor,<\/strong><strong> and I have a greater sense of honor than him, and Allah has a greater sense of honor than me<\/strong>.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 1498<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <em><strong>Sahih<\/strong> <\/em>(authentic) according to Muslim<\/p>\n<p align=\"right\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0647\u064f\u0631\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0631\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0633\u064e\u0639\u0652\u062f\u064f \u0628\u0652\u0646\u064f \u0639\u064f\u0628\u064e\u0627\u062f\u064e\u0629\u064e \u064a\u064e\u0627 \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0644\u064e\u0648\u0652 \u0648\u064e\u062c\u064e\u062f\u0652\u062a\u064f \u0645\u064e\u0639\u064e \u0623\u064e\u0647\u0652\u0644\u0650\u064a \u0631\u064e\u062c\u064f\u0644\u064b\u0627 \u0644\u064e\u0645\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0645\u064e\u063